    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4] </span>thick steaks from the centre of the <strong>cauliflower<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>(keep any leftovers, chop them into florets, then roast for a tasty snack!)</p><p>Add the <strong>cauliflower steaks </strong>to a baking tray, then drizzle the <strong>tamari soy sauce</strong> all over and put the tray in the oven for 30-35 min or until golden and tender, turning once halfway</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-cauliflower-steak-with-charred-veg-and-chimichurri/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the<strong> waxy potatoes</strong> in half and add them to one side of a separate baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-cauliflower-steak-with-charred-veg-and-chimichurri/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the<strong> parsley</strong> and<strong> coriander </strong>roughly</p><p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop the <strong>spring onions</strong> in half</p><p>Cut the <strong>red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon), then chop each half into 3 pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-cauliflower-steak-with-charred-veg-and-chimichurri/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had 15 min, remove the tray from the oven and add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and <strong>halved spring onions</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 15 min further or until the peppers are softened and charred and the potatoes are crisp</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-cauliflower-steak-with-charred-veg-and-chimichurri/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> chopped herbs </strong>to a <strong>pestle & mortar </strong>with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Grind to a course paste, then add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> with the<strong> red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and the <strong>chopped shallot</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good stir \u2013 this is your <strong>chimichurri</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-cauliflower-steak-with-charred-veg-and-chimichurri/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(not a fan of raw garlic? Just add a little!) with the<strong> mayo</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-cauliflower-steak-with-charred-veg-and-chimichurri/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the cauliflower steaks are almost done, sprinkle the <strong>pumpkin seeds </strong>over the tray and return it to the oven for 2-3 min or until lightly toasted</p><p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-cauliflower-steak-with-charred-veg-and-chimichurri/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cauliflower steaks</strong> with the <strong>rocket</strong>,<strong> charred veg</strong> and <strong>crispy potatoes</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>chimichurri </strong>all over the steaks, garnish with the<strong> toasted pumpkin seeds</strong> and serve with a dollop of <strong>garlic mayo </strong>and enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Got a BBQ? Grab the plates and fire up the barbie. This recipe is a grill's best friend.</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
